    "name": "Grid Independence and Spatial Convergence Verification",
    "description": "Systematic grid refinement study conducted on three mesh densities (coarse 2.1M cells, medium 5.8M cells, fine 14.2M cells) to verify spatial discretization convergence for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. Richardson extrapolation applied to shear-stress-derived hemolysis index at the five nominal CPB operating points. Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Celik et al. (2008) methodology. Target GCI < 5% on the fine-to-medium pair for all operating conditions.",
